rComments: Joanna is very sweet and an amazing professor. You can tell that she is very passionate about her courses. I took innovators and their ideas with her as a first year seminar. She is suppper funny and her lectures are very fun. The material is very interesting. However, there were a lot of writing assignments and you HAVE to use library research.

Great Professor, very knowledgeable and passionate about the material, readings and lecture notes are not necessary. However, theyre is a lot of writing assignments so if youre not the best at English and getting your point you may not get a great mark. If your looking for a bird course, this is it. Life science is hell and this is light work.

I've had this prof twice, and she's the best. She's passionate about the material, and comes up with lots of ways to keep everyone engaged and participating. She always makes herself available for help, or to talk through assignments. It's rare to have a prof at UofT who cares about their students so much! Definitely recommend taking her class.

You have to bring hard copies of your essays. Professor did not post marks online, so it was hard to keep track. I did not have a chance to see the mark for the last two assignments. And then out of sudden I got the final mark on my transcript.
